reviews.text: The beef noodle and the deep fried fish cake were delicious. It could be even better if they were less salty. I had to drink a lot of water after the meal.
Food is nice at reasonable price
It would be good to serve lime & bean sprout and or other pho accompaniments without asking for them. Generally, food were mainly HK tastes.
Fair food but rude staffs

I used to visit this eatery to sample Vietnamese style submarine sandwich and Vietnamese style drip coffee, which was quite satisfactory. But as I visited there few weeks ago, the sandwiches were off the menu, and I had to order beef pho soup noodle instead. As I tasted it, it was clear to me that the beef which was supposed to be served raw and cooked naturally in very hot soup, in order to retain its tenderness, was pre-boiled before it was put onto the noodle bowl. It resulted in the he meat served very tough and bland. Then I ordered the Vietnamese style drip coffee which I used to order with sandwitch...the hot water for the drip was far less than it used to be but it costs HK$35 for a cup of very inadequate cup of coffee. The decline of the quality of this eatery is disappointing to say the least. I know I will NEVER visit this place again. It is waste of time, and waste of money.

reviews.text:
周六下午茶
呢到竟然有全日餐食～驚喜加分～
魚柳大大件～

おいしかった。私は冷たい物を頼んだが、現地の方は温かい物を頼んでいた。外してしまったかもしれません。
ただしそれでも十分においしかったです
今午(星期六，一點半)點咗個咖喱魚柳飯，味道還好，但咸咗好多，要改良。收$56，價錢在佐敦唔貴啦，用料都好足，有好多塊魚，包餐㚫茶。因在内街，忙得來也不用等，不過厠所及去那裏的路，衛生便很差要改善了。
晚上叫個梁瓜班腩飯堂食非常差！飯也凍冰冰、班腩好惺味地好難食！
佐敦地鐵站隔離，食物質素一般， 環境很嘈吵
